ce:section.ce:para:
The storage stability of CQDs and CQDs-PAMAM complexes was studied to evaluate any changes in the fluorescent property of CQDs as well as CQDs-PAMAM complexes within 3 months at −20 °C, as the refrigerated condition is best for CQDs storage. The results of the stability study revealed that CQDs along with its complexes with full and half generations PAMAM dendrimers showed no significant change in fluorescence intensity up to 2 months without any sign of precipitations (
                        Fig. 10

                        ). The CQDs showed around a 3 % decrease in fluorescence intensity after 90 days. The full generations PAMAM dendrimer complexes i.e., CQDs-PAMAM G4 and CQDs-PAMAM G5 showed around 30 % drop in fluorescence intensity after 90 days although it is in the detectable range. On the other hand, half generations PAMAM dendrimers complexes showed around 24 % decrease in fluorescence intensity after 90 days. Overall, the CQDs-PAMAM complexes showed good stability over a period of 2 months without any significant reduction in fluorescence intensity, whereas CQDs shown excellent stability over period of 3 months. However, despite of some decrease in fluorescent intensity after 90 days, the CQDs-PAMAM dendrimer complexes showed fluorescent intensity which was sufficiently strong enough for biological imaging. Further, strategies like surface conjugation may also be explored to provide stronger protection for fluorescent intensity of CQDs-PAMAM dendrimer complexes.
